# 🧠 OS Concept 2: Backpressure in Distributed Systems

🔥 Important scalability concept.

---

## 1️⃣ Problem

Producer sends requests faster than consumer can handle.

Result:

❌ overload
❌ queue buildup
❌ failures

---

## Solution

Backpressure slows incoming requests.

---

## 🧠 Real-World Analogy

Traffic police slowing vehicles entering crowded road.

---

## Examples

* message queues
* streaming systems
* APIs

---

## Why Important?

✔ prevents crashes
✔ improves stability

---

## 🎯 Placement Question

**Q: What is backpressure?**

👉 Mechanism used to control overload by slowing request flow.

---

## 🧠 Memory Trick

```text id="9k1xqw"
Too much traffic → slow input
```

---

# ⚙️ COA Concept 3: Approximate Computing

🔥 Future energy-efficient computing topic.

---

## 1️⃣ Simple Idea

Not all applications require perfectly exact results.

Approximate computing allows:

👉 small accuracy tradeoff for huge efficiency gain.

---

## Examples

* image processing
* AI inference
* multimedia systems

---

## Why Useful?

✔ lower power usage
✔ faster execution
✔ reduced hardware cost

---

## 🧠 Real-World Analogy

Estimating crowd size instead of exact counting.

---

## Tradeoff

```text id="2r7mvp"
Slight accuracy loss
↓
Big performance gain
```

---

## 🎯 Placement Question

**Q: Why approximate computing useful?**

👉 Because some applications tolerate small inaccuracies for better efficiency.

---

## 🧠 Memory Trick

```text id="5x8qzn"
Small error, big efficiency
```

---

# ⚙️ COA Concept 4: AI Hardware Scheduling

🔥 Modern AI infrastructure concept.

---

## 1️⃣ Problem

AI workloads share:

* GPUs
* TPUs
* memory
* bandwidth

Need efficient scheduling.

---

## Goals

✔ maximize utilization
✔ reduce waiting
✔ balance workloads

---

## Example

Multiple AI jobs on same GPU cluster.

Scheduler decides:

```text id="7n3qwt"
who runs where and when
```

---

## Why Important?

Poor scheduling causes:

❌ idle hardware
❌ slow training
❌ resource waste

---

## 🔗 Connection

Similar idea to:

👉 CPU scheduling in OS

---

## 🎯 Placement Question

**Q: Why AI hardware scheduling important?**

👉 Because AI systems require efficient allocation of expensive compute resources.

---

## 🧠 Memory Trick

```text id="3m9xvk"
Schedule GPUs efficiently
```

